HEADWORD: Sarcology
<hw>Sar*col"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sarco-</ets> + <ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>sarcologie</ets>.]</ety> <def>That part of anatomy which treats of
the soft parts. It includes myology, angiology, neurology, and
splanchnology.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sarcoma</ent>⟦br⟧
